						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the Surabhēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya I, 2nd Regnal year (655-56 A.D.).</p>						

						<p>This inscription states that the mother of <hi rend="italic">Ujēnīpisācha</hi> gave a grant of land measuring 150 <hi rend="italic">(Nivartanas)</hi> to Gōvṛishāṇa-Bhaṭṭāraka. (pub. Ep.Ind. Vol. XXIX pp. 160 ff).</p>						

